Above classes, you will find the concept of cluster.  A cluster is a group of related classes.  Clusters are a property of the method, enabling managers to organize the development into teams.  As we have already seen (section 

				tutorial-04.xml#41726
			 ) they also play a central role in the lifecycle model.  Clusters are an organizational concept, not a form of module, and do not require an Eiffel language construct.
